Welcome to Agros 2D.

This manual is intended for Debian-based systems. For other systems is very similar.

Requirements
============

You must first install the needed requirements. They are Hermes2D (http://www.hpfem.org/hermes2d), Nokia Qt 4.5 (http://www.qtsoftware.com/products), Qwt 5.0 (http://qwt.sourceforge.net) and Triangle (http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~quake/triangle.html).

Install the required libraries:

$ apt-get install libqt4-dev qt4-dev-tools libsuitesparse-dev libqwt5-qt4-dev libtriangle-1.6

Hermes2D can not install from the repositories, but it is necessary to compile it.

To compile Agros 2D you need qmake, and q++, install this packages:

$ apt-get install qmake q++

Documentation
=============

Agros 2D manual is available from the program by pressing F1. To generate this help run:

qhelpgenerator ./doc/help/agros2d.qhp -o ./doc/help/agros2d.qch

or

$ ./agros2d.debian.sh -h

Location
========

Agros 2D is available in two languages (Czech and English). To generate files with localization run:

lrelease ./lang/*.ts ./lang/*.qm

or

$ ./agros2d.debian.sh -l

Compilation
===========

For compile run:

$ qmake agros2d.pro
$ make

or

$ ./agros2d.debian.sh -c

For build binary package run:

dpkg-buildpackage -sgpg -rfakeroot

or

$ ./agros2d.debian.sh -p

Tips
====

To simplify the described steps (generate documentation and location, compilation, create package) run:

$ ./agros2d.debian.sh -a
